This repository introduces a hybrid cryptographic framework designed for the generation and metaheuristic optimization of robust S-Boxes, which serve as fundamental components in symmetric block ciphers such as AES. The implementation utilizes a two-stage pipeline: an initial algebraic construction phase—employing cubic polynomial mapping, finite field inversion over GF($2^8$), and affine transformations—to establish baseline cryptographic properties, followed by an evolutionary optimization phase. This second stage leverages a Genetic Algorithm (GA) to refine the S-Box population through elitism, crossover, and mutation strategies, allowing for the iterative improvement of the S-Box based on target performance metrics. By combining deterministic algebraic construction with iterative heuristic search, the project functions as a scalable research tool for investigating the convergence of evolutionary algorithms in finding high-performance cryptographic primitives, complete with integrated benchmarking utilities to track execution overhead across each stage of the pipeline.
